 t = \sqrt{\frac{x-1}{x+1}} \\ x = \frac{1+t^2}{1-t^2} \\ dx = \frac{4t}{(1-t^2)^2}\;dt = \frac{4t}{(1-t)^2(1+t)^2}\;dt \\ \int\left(1+\sqrt{\frac{x-1}{x+1}}\right)^2 dx = \int (1+t)^2\frac{4t}{(1-t)^2(1+t)^2}\;dt = \int \frac{4t}{(1-t)^2}\;dt \\ \qquad = \int\left(\frac{4}{t-1} + \frac{4}{(t-1)^2}\right) dt = 4\log(t-1) - \frac{4}{t-1} +C 
